        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 6:11PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 611 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ronda, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elkin...
Jonesville...
Ronda...
Pleasant Hill...
State Road...
Clingman...
and Benham.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
